
OOPs

a) Object Oriented Programming is a methodology to design a program using object and classes
b) It simplifies the software development and maintenance by providing the below defined concepts:

  a) Class:-
       1. Class is a blueprint from which you can create an object
       2. The instruction to create an object is present in class
       3. Class doesn't not exist. It has properties( variables) and functions(methods).

  b) Object:-
       1. An entity that has state and behavior is known as object.
       2. For Example:- A dog is an object because is has state like color, name, breed etc and fucntions as wagging the tail, barking, eating etc.



